==English==

===Etymology===
The name Nina is present in several languages, including Russian, Romanian, Spanish, Persian, and some Native American languages. The English name is from [[Antonina]], from [[Anthony]], from [[Antonius]], ultimately from Etruscan (not Greek).

===Pronunciation===
* NEE-na
* ŋi-na
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːnə|-iːnə]]

===Proper noun===
'''Nina'''

#A common female [[given name]].  
#Short form of names that end in -nina.
#The Babylonian goddess of the watery deep and daughter of Ea.

